      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Sure, here are some universal rules for being a global professional:\n\n1. Dress appropriately: Always dress according to the cultural norms of the country you are visiting. For example, in many Asian countries, conservative attire is expected, while Western countries may have more relaxed dress codes.\n2. Respect local customs: Be aware of and respect local customs and traditions. This might include greeting people in a certain way, using formal language, or observing religious practices.\n3. Be punctual: Timekeeping can vary greatly around the world. In some cultures, being late is seen as disrespectful, while in others, it is more relaxed. Make sure to research the time expectations of the country you are visiting.\n4. Use polite language: Always use polite and respectful language when speaking to others, regardless of their cultural background.\n5. Be aware of non-verbal cues: Different cultures have different non-verbal communication norms. Be observant and respectful of these differences, such as eye contact, gestures, and personal space.\n6. Understand and respect gender roles: Gender roles can vary greatly across cultures. Be respectful and understanding of these differences when interacting with others.\n7. Be mindful of food and drink etiquette: Different cultures have different food and drink customs. Be",
